## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

This is a textbook **"coverage-only" test suite**. Every production method is called (achieving high line coverage), but almost nothing is actually verified. A mutation testing tool would kill nearly every test here.

---

### 🔴 CRITICAL — Missing Assertions (Assertionless Tests)

These tests execute production code but verify **zero behavior**. They pass even if the implementation is completely wrong.

**1. `AddProduct_Works` (line 17–21) — No assertion at all**

The product is added but never retrieved to confirm it was stored.

```csharp
// FIX:
_catalog.AddProduct(product);
var result = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNotNull(result);
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", result.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, result.Price);
```

**2. `UpdatePrice_Works` (line 32–36) — No assertion at all**

`UpdatePrice` is called but the new price is never read back. A no-op implementation would pass.

```csharp
// FIX:
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", updated.Name); // ensure name wasn't clobbered
```

**3. `RemoveProduct_Works` (line 38–43) — No assertion at all**

Removal is never confirmed. The product could still be in the store.

```csharp
// FIX:
_catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
```

**4. `GetProductCount_Works` (line 63–66) — No assertion at all**

The count is not even captured into a variable for assertion. On an empty store, this is doubly useless.

```csharp
// FIX:
_catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
_catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-002", "Gadget", 19.99m));
Assert.AreEqual(2, _catalog.GetProductCount());
```

**5. `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (line 68–74) — No assertion at all**

A 10% discount is applied but no price is checked afterwards. The discount formula (`Price * (1 - fraction)`) is completely unverified.

```csharp
// FIX:
_catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);
var w = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
var g = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-002");
Assert.AreEqual(8.991m, w!.Price);   // 9.99 * 0.90
Assert.AreEqual(17.991m, g!.Price);  // 19.99 * 0.90
```

