### Summary

| Severity | Count | Pattern |
|---|---|---|
| 🔴 Critical | 6 | **Zero assertions** — test calls method, verifies nothing |
| 🟠 High | 4 | **Non-null-only assertions** — verifies existence, not correctness |
| 🟡 Medium | 6+ | **Missing negative/edge paths** — error scenarios untested |

**Root cause**: Every test follows the same template — call the method, maybe check `IsNotNull`, done. This is a classic "coverage-farming" pattern: line coverage reaches 95%+ because every code path is *executed*, but no behavior is *verified*. A mutation testing tool (e.g., Stryker.NET) would show a near-zero mutation kill rate despite the high coverage number.
